Data availability

            SPEI data are form Chen et al.13 NDVI data are form AVHRR GIMMS-3G+ (https://daac.ornl.gov/VEGETATION/guides/Global_Veg_Greenness_GIMMS_3G.html) and MODIS MOD13C1 (https://www.earthdata.nasa.gov/data/catalog/lpcloud-mod13c1-006). C-band VOD data are obtained from Wang et al.124 Temperature data are from the fifth generation ECMWF atmospheric reanalysis of the global climate (ERA5) (https://cds.climate.copernicus.eu/datasets/reanalysis-era5-land-monthly-means?tab=download). Vapour pressure deficit (VPD), potential evapotranspiration (PET) and soil moisture data are available at https://climate.northwestknowledge.net/TERRACLIMATE/index_directDownloads.php. Water table depth data are downloaded from http://files.ntsg.umt.edu/data/LPDR_v2/. Max root depth data are provided by Fan et al.52 Canopy height data are acquired from https://data.caltech.edu/records/mwhhr-0rq03. Species richness data are available at https://anthroecology.org/anthromes/plantbiodiversity/. Burned-area data are available at https://zenodo.org/records/7668424. Human footprint index data are obtained from https://figshare.com/articles/Fig./An_annual_global_terrestrial_Human_Footprint_dataset_from_2000_to_2018/16571064/7. Land-cover data are provided by https://data.casearth.cn/thematic/glc_fcs30/314. Climate region data are downloaded from https://www.gloh2o.org/koppen/. The spatial delineation of intact forests and managed forest is obtained from Lesiv et al.121
          Code availability

            The code used for this study is available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18345236 (ref. 138).
